1
00:00:01,961 --> 00:00:02,962
SHE'S COMING TO.

2
00:00:02,962 --> 00:00:08,133
[ GROANS ]
LET ME GO!

3
00:00:08,133 --> 00:00:09,134
LET ME GO!

4
00:00:09,134 --> 00:00:11,052
-STOP!
-I'LL KILL YOU!

5
00:00:11,052 --> 00:00:12,220
WE'RE NOT GOING TO HURT YOU!

6
00:00:12,220 --> 00:00:14,890
YOU LIAR. NO!

7
00:00:14,890 --> 00:00:16,892
GET AWAY FROM ME! NO!

8
00:00:16,892 --> 00:00:18,936
[ SCREAMING ]

9
00:00:21,689 --> 00:00:25,400
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

10
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:28,445
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

11
00:00:28,445 --> 00:00:32,407
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

12
00:00:32,407 --> 00:00:36,119
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

13
00:00:36,119 --> 00:00:40,457
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

14
00:00:40,457 --> 00:00:44,169
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

15
00:00:44,169 --> 00:00:48,089
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

16
00:00:48,089 --> 00:00:51,218
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

17
00:00:51,218 --> 00:00:53,637
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

18
00:00:53,637 --> 00:00:55,931
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

19
00:00:55,931 --> 00:00:59,018
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

20
00:00:59,018 --> 00:01:03,939
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

21
00:01:03,939 --> 00:01:06,942
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

22
00:01:06,942 --> 00:01:11,405
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

23
00:01:11,405 --> 00:01:14,366
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

24
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:20,039
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

25
00:01:20,039 --> 00:01:21,874
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

26
00:01:21,874 --> 00:01:23,959
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

27
00:01:23,959 --> 00:01:27,838
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

28
00:01:27,838 --> 00:01:31,884
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

29
00:01:41,309 --> 00:01:43,102
THE DAMAGE IS MORE SEVERE
THAN I EXPECTED.

30
00:01:43,102 --> 00:01:44,730
-CAN YOU REVERSE IT?
-I'M NOT CERTAIN.

31
00:01:44,730 --> 00:01:45,981
[ GRUNTING ]

32
00:01:45,981 --> 00:01:47,566
-WHAT'S HE DOING?
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.

33
00:01:47,566 --> 00:01:49,860
-HE'S TRYING TO HELP YOU.
-HE'S TRYING TO KILL ME!

34
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:52,613
LIKE YOU KILLED THE OTHERS!
MURDERERS!

35
00:01:52,613 --> 00:01:54,239
GET AWAY!

36
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:56,366
NO!

37
00:01:57,952 --> 00:02:00,120
[ SCREAMING ]

38
00:02:24,853 --> 00:02:27,106
I TALKED WITH CHEF AT DINNER.

39
00:02:27,106 --> 00:02:29,316
HE'S A LITTLE WORRIED
ABOUT THE CREW.

40
00:02:30,985 --> 00:02:32,903
PEOPLE ARE SKIPPING MEALS.

41
00:02:32,903 --> 00:02:34,738
HE FIGURES
THEY'RE EITHER TOO BUSY

42
00:02:34,738 --> 00:02:36,824
OR THE STRESS OF THIS MISSION
IS STARTING TO GET TO THEM.

43
00:02:36,824 --> 00:02:39,367
I HAVEN'T HAD
MUCH OF AN APPETITE MYSELF.

44
00:02:41,328 --> 00:02:43,538
MOVIE NIGHT'S BEEN ON HOLD
SINCE WE ENTERED THE EXPANSE.

45
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:46,541
MAYBE WE SHOULD
START IT UP AGAIN.

46
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:47,960
THERE'LL BE PLENTY OF TIME
FOR MOVIES

47
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:51,672
AFTER WE'VE DEALT
WITH THE XINDI.

48
00:02:51,672 --> 00:02:54,591
NO ONE HATES THE XINDI
MORE THAN I DO, CAPTAIN.

49
00:02:54,591 --> 00:02:58,219
BUT I'M TELLING YOU,
THIS CREW NEEDS A LITTLE R&amp;R.

50
00:02:58,219 --> 00:03:02,057
UNLESS YOU WANT PHLOX TO START
MEDICATING PEOPLE, WE GOT TO...

51
00:03:02,057 --> 00:03:03,934
WE GOT TO FIND A WAY
TO BOOST MORALE.

52
00:03:03,934 --> 00:03:06,728
WHAT DID YOU HAVE IN MIND?

53
00:03:06,728 --> 00:03:09,356
I WAS THINKING ABOUT A COMEDY.

54
00:03:09,356 --> 00:03:13,152
ONE OF THE CLASSIC
HOPE AND CROSBY PICTURES.

55
00:03:13,152 --> 00:03:14,569
GOOD CHOICE.

56
00:03:16,613 --> 00:03:18,239
CAPTAIN?

57
00:03:18,239 --> 00:03:21,743
WE'VE BEEN REVIEWING
SOME OF THESE XINDI STAR CHARTS.

58
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:23,453
TRIP THOUGHT THEY MIGHT BE ABLE
TO HELP US FIGURE OUT

59
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:25,998
IF THERE ARE ANY MORE
SPATIAL ANOMALIES IN THE REGION.

60
00:03:25,998 --> 00:03:27,290
I WOULD HAVE HELPED YOU DO THAT.

61
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:28,625
IT'S LATE.

62
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:30,544
I DIDN'T WANT
TO GET YOU OUT OF BED.

63
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:34,548
BESIDES, OUR RESIDENT INSOMNIAC
WAS LOOKING FOR SOMETHING TO DO.

64
00:03:34,548 --> 00:03:37,926
[ BEEPING ]

65
00:03:37,926 --> 00:03:40,512
YOU HAVE PLANS TUESDAY NIGHT?

66
00:03:40,512 --> 00:03:42,806
NOT AT THE MOMENT.

67
00:03:42,806 --> 00:03:44,641
MESS HALL, 1900 HOURS.

68
00:03:46,101 --> 00:03:47,352
MOVIE NIGHT?

69
00:03:47,352 --> 00:03:48,896
BACK BY POPULAR DEMAND.

70
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:50,438
-[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
-BRIDGE TO CAPTAIN ARCHER.

71
00:03:50,438 --> 00:03:51,899
GO AHEAD.

72
00:03:51,899 --> 00:03:54,735
I'M PICKING UP AN AUTOMATED
DISTRESS CALL, SIR.

73
00:03:54,735 --> 00:03:56,070
IT'S VULCAN.

74
00:03:58,530 --> 00:03:59,865
HAVE YOU TRIED HAILING THEM?

75
00:03:59,865 --> 00:04:01,033
SEVERAL TIMES.

76
00:04:01,033 --> 00:04:03,284
I'M ON MY WAY.

77
00:04:07,539 --> 00:04:08,749
WHERE ARE THEY?

78
00:04:08,749 --> 00:04:13,420
3.2 LIGHT-YEARS,
BEARING 016 MARK 12.

79
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:18,258
I RECOGNIZE
THE TRANSPONDER FREQUENCY.

80
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:19,593
IT'S THE<i> SELEYA.</i>

81
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:22,303
THEY ENTERED THE EXPANSE
NINE MONTHS AGO.

82
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:26,600
KEEP HAILING THEM.

83
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:29,061
SET A COURSE.

84
00:04:53,043 --> 00:04:56,130
THE ASTEROIDS ARE MOVING
IN A CHAOTIC FASHION.

85
00:04:56,130 --> 00:04:58,339
THEIR PATHS ARE UNPREDICTABLE.

86
00:04:58,339 --> 00:05:00,842
MAY BE THE RESULT
OF SOME SPATIAL ANOMALIES.

87
00:05:00,842 --> 00:05:02,219
WHERE'S THE VULCAN SHIP?

88
00:05:02,219 --> 00:05:04,554
APPROXIMATELY
2,000 KILOMETERS DEAD AHEAD.

89
00:05:04,554 --> 00:05:07,557
I CAN GUESS WHY THEY WERE
INTERESTED IN THIS FIELD.

90
00:05:07,557 --> 00:05:09,268
THE ASTEROIDS ARE LOADED
WITH TRELLIUM ORE.

91
00:05:12,146 --> 00:05:15,149
IT LOOKS A LITTLE TOO CROWDED
IN THERE FOR<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

92
00:05:15,149 --> 00:05:16,483
WAKE UP MR. REED.

93
00:05:16,483 --> 00:05:18,193
TELL HIM TO MEET US
IN THE LAUNCH BAY.

94
00:05:18,193 --> 00:05:19,527
AYE, SIR.

95
00:05:19,527 --> 00:05:21,905
TRY TO GET YOUR HANDS
ON SOME OF THAT ORE.

96
00:05:21,905 --> 00:05:23,157
T'POL.

97
00:05:32,291 --> 00:05:35,127
[ BEEPING ]

98
00:05:35,127 --> 00:05:37,462
STARBOARD BOW, 340 METERS.

99
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:38,964
I SEE IT.

100
00:05:45,971 --> 00:05:48,389
[ THUDDING ]

101
00:05:48,389 --> 00:05:51,392
NO DAMAGE, THOUGH WE MAY NEED
A FRESH COAT OF PAINT.

102
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:54,021
HOW MUCH FARTHER?

103
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:55,939
1,200 KILOMETERS.

104
00:05:57,398 --> 00:06:00,194
I COULD TAKE THE HELM
IF YOU'D LIKE.

105
00:06:00,194 --> 00:06:02,029
MAYBE ON THE WAY BACK.

106
00:06:04,363 --> 00:06:07,201
SO WHAT ELSE DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT THE<i> SELEYA?</i>

107
00:06:07,201 --> 00:06:08,743
A GREAT DEAL.

108
00:06:08,743 --> 00:06:11,246
I SERVED ON IT FOR OVER A YEAR.

109
00:06:11,246 --> 00:06:12,497
IT WAS MY LAST ASSIGNMENT

110
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:14,415
BEFORE JOINING
THE CONSULATE ON EARTH.

111
00:06:14,415 --> 00:06:17,502
I WAS THE DEPUTY SCIENCE OFFICER
UNDER CAPTAIN VORIS.

112
00:06:17,502 --> 00:06:20,172
ANY IDEA WHAT THEY
WERE DOING IN THE EXPANSE?

113
00:06:20,172 --> 00:06:22,632
THEY WERE ATTEMPTING TO CHART
THE THERMOBARIC PERIMETER.

114
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:24,383
AFTER SEVERAL DAYS,
THEY REPORTED

115
00:06:24,383 --> 00:06:28,222
THAT THEY'D BECOME CAUGHT
IN SOME KIND OF SUBSPACE EDDY

116
00:06:28,222 --> 00:06:30,765
AND WERE BEING PULLED
INTO THE EXPANSE.

117
00:06:30,765 --> 00:06:32,893
IT WAS THEIR FINAL TRANSMISSION.

118
00:06:34,686 --> 00:06:37,356
THE<i> VANKAARA</i>
<i>WAS SENT TO FIND THEM.</i>

119
00:06:37,356 --> 00:06:40,234
YOU ALREADY KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO THAT CREW.

120
00:06:40,234 --> 00:06:42,652
LET'S HOPE THE<i> SELEYA</i>
<i>FARED A LITTLE BETTER.</i>

121
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:44,445
[ BEEPING ]

122
00:06:44,445 --> 00:06:46,156
DIRECTLY AHEAD, 200 METERS.

123
00:06:46,156 --> 00:06:47,908
HANG ON!

124
00:07:04,383 --> 00:07:06,551
GOOD ISOTOPE DENSITY.

125
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:09,012
WE SHOULD GET AT LEAST
HALF A KILO OUT OF THIS ONE.

126
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:14,017
[ GRUNTS ] LET'S TRY FOR
SOMETHING BIGGER THIS TIME.

127
00:07:18,605 --> 00:07:21,066
HOW ABOUT, UH, THIS ONE?

128
00:07:21,066 --> 00:07:22,150
[ BEEPING ]

129
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:23,902
I'VE GOT A LOCK.

130
00:07:27,197 --> 00:07:28,907
TRAVIS?

131
00:07:31,118 --> 00:07:33,828
THERE'S AN OVERLOAD
IN THE RESEQUENCER.

132
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:34,996
SHUT IT DOWN.

133
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:36,123
I CAN'T.

134
00:07:36,123 --> 00:07:37,498
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

135
00:07:49,386 --> 00:07:51,888
[ BUZZES ]

136
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:53,890
OH, THIS THING'S USELESS!

137
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:57,060
THE COILS ARE FUSED.

138
00:07:57,060 --> 00:08:01,106
WHAT IF I COULD PUT A SHUTTLEPOD
DOWN ON ONE OF THE BIG ONES?

139
00:08:01,106 --> 00:08:02,774
THEY'RE PRETTY UNPREDICTABLE.

140
00:08:02,774 --> 00:08:04,276
YOU SURE YOU COULD LAND SAFELY?

141
00:08:04,276 --> 00:08:05,568
I CAN TRY.

142
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:11,741
THIS'LL BE A NEW ONE
FOR THE MAINTENANCE CREW.

143
00:08:25,005 --> 00:08:27,174
MAIN POWER'S OFFLINE.

144
00:08:27,174 --> 00:08:29,426
THEIR HULL'S
TAKEN QUITE A BEATING.

145
00:08:29,426 --> 00:08:31,970
LIFE SUPPORT?

146
00:08:31,970 --> 00:08:35,223
MINIMAL. DECKS 12 AND 13
HAVE DECOMPRESSED.

147
00:08:35,223 --> 00:08:37,809
I'M READING MULTIPLE BIOSIGNS.

148
00:08:39,144 --> 00:08:40,728
[ BEEP ]

149
00:08:40,728 --> 00:08:43,440
THIS IS CAPTAIN ARCHER
OF THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

150
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,233
PLEASE RESPOND.

151
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:50,322
[ BEEP ]

152
00:08:50,322 --> 00:08:52,366
<i>SELEYA,</i> COME IN.

153
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:58,997
THE STARBOARD DOCKING PORT
IS STILL INTACT.

154
00:09:01,375 --> 00:09:04,419
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLING ]

155
00:09:07,214 --> 00:09:09,216
[ GRUNTS ]

156
00:09:44,792 --> 00:09:47,170
[ BEEPING ]

157
00:09:47,170 --> 00:09:48,547
CAPTAIN?

158
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:56,179
THEY WERE LINING THIS BULKHEAD
WITH TRELLIUM.

159
00:09:56,179 --> 00:09:57,931
THEY DIDN'T GET VERY FAR.

160
00:09:57,931 --> 00:10:00,600
I'M READING BIOSIGNS
ON THIS DECK.

161
00:10:02,561 --> 00:10:04,354
I CAN'T ISOLATE THEM.

162
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:10,944
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

163
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:15,865
TAKE STARBOARD.

164
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:23,582
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

165
00:10:48,315 --> 00:10:49,816
VULCAN BLOOD.

166
00:10:54,237 --> 00:10:56,573
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

167
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:06,791
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLING ]

168
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:17,093
[ CLANKING ]

169
00:11:23,682 --> 00:11:26,060
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLING ]

170
00:11:30,607 --> 00:11:32,526
ONE BIOSIGN.

171
00:11:34,986 --> 00:11:36,821
[ DOOR BUZZES ]

172
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:51,294
[ DOOR CLICKS ]

173
00:11:57,842 --> 00:11:59,052
AAH!

174
00:11:59,052 --> 00:12:01,137
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

175
00:12:11,022 --> 00:12:12,524
UGH!

176
00:12:14,317 --> 00:12:15,485
AAH!

177
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:34,546
YOU ALL RIGHT?

178
00:12:37,006 --> 00:12:38,592
T'POL?

179
00:12:39,551 --> 00:12:40,927
I'M FINE.

180
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:48,226
HIS SYNAPTIC PATHWAYS
HAVE BEEN SEVERELY DAMAGED.

181
00:12:48,226 --> 00:12:51,062
LET'S GET HIM IN THE POD.

182
00:12:51,062 --> 00:12:52,355
[ CLANK ]

183
00:12:52,355 --> 00:12:53,898
CAPTAIN!

184
00:12:56,568 --> 00:12:57,736
KEEP BACK.

185
00:13:07,621 --> 00:13:08,747
ARCHER TO REED.

186
00:13:08,747 --> 00:13:09,914
GO AHEAD, SIR.

187
00:13:09,914 --> 00:13:11,332
HAVE YOU COME ACROSS ANYONE?

188
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:12,292
NOT YET.

189
00:13:12,292 --> 00:13:14,001
WATCH YOURSELF.

190
00:13:14,001 --> 00:13:16,795
SOMETHING'S HAPPENED TO THEM.
THEY'VE BECOME VIOLENT.

191
00:13:16,795 --> 00:13:18,131
AYE, SIR.

192
00:13:20,007 --> 00:13:21,676
[ GRUNTS ]

193
00:13:24,929 --> 00:13:26,473
[ GROANS ]

194
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:34,689
[ GROANS ]

195
00:13:38,735 --> 00:13:41,070
[ GRUNTS ]

196
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:42,572
AAH!

197
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:54,542
UH!

198
00:13:57,211 --> 00:13:58,379
[ CHOKING ]

199
00:14:02,008 --> 00:14:03,134
[ GASPS ]

200
00:14:03,134 --> 00:14:04,719
LIEUTENANT, YOU OKAY?

201
00:14:04,719 --> 00:14:06,887
YEAH.

202
00:14:06,887 --> 00:14:08,556
WHAT HAPPENED TO THEM?

203
00:14:10,391 --> 00:14:13,978
SEVEN MORE.
THAT DIRECTION. 30 METERS.

204
00:14:13,978 --> 00:14:15,104
CAPTAIN.

205
00:14:16,189 --> 00:14:18,024
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

206
00:14:22,153 --> 00:14:23,488
[ GUN CLICKS ]

207
00:14:23,488 --> 00:14:24,447
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

208
00:14:24,447 --> 00:14:25,615
STUN ISN'T WORKING.

209
00:14:25,615 --> 00:14:27,367
WE SHOULD SET OUR WEAPONS
TO KILL.

210
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:29,536
THESE ARE VULCAN OFFICERS,
AND WE'RE ON A RESCUE MISSION.

211
00:14:29,536 --> 00:14:32,664
WITH RESPECT, MA'AM, THEY DON'T
SEEM TO WANT OUR HELP!

212
00:14:32,664 --> 00:14:35,124
YOU HEARD ME.

213
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:37,460
KEEP YOUR WEAPONS ON STUN.

214
00:14:37,460 --> 00:14:39,337
YES, SIR.

215
00:14:45,051 --> 00:14:46,845
CAPTAIN, OVER HERE.

216
00:14:54,185 --> 00:14:55,353
WHAT ARE THEY DOING?

217
00:15:02,777 --> 00:15:05,822
WE'RE FROM
THE STARFLEET SHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

218
00:15:10,702 --> 00:15:11,870
DO YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

219
00:15:16,957 --> 00:15:19,168
[ GRUNTS ]

220
00:15:22,046 --> 00:15:23,548
IS THERE ANOTHER WAY
TO THE AIRLOCK?

221
00:15:23,548 --> 00:15:24,674
NO.

222
00:15:24,674 --> 00:15:26,718
[ DOOR CREAKING ]

223
00:15:36,227 --> 00:15:37,604
THAT WAY.

224
00:15:37,604 --> 00:15:39,647
GO.

225
00:15:50,991 --> 00:15:52,159
GO ON.

226
00:15:56,873 --> 00:15:59,375
[ GRUNTS ]

227
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:15,475
ARCHER TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

228
00:16:19,103 --> 00:16:21,105
<i>ENTERPRISE,</i> RESPOND!

229
00:16:22,857 --> 00:16:24,609
IF THEIR COM SYSTEM'S INTACT,

230
00:16:24,609 --> 00:16:26,694
WE MAY BE ABLE TO CONTACT
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> FROM THE BRIDGE.

231
00:16:26,694 --> 00:16:28,279
WHERE IS IT?

232
00:16:28,279 --> 00:16:30,114
SEVEN DECKS ABOVE US.

233
00:16:30,114 --> 00:16:31,282
SEVEN?

234
00:16:31,282 --> 00:16:33,409
HOW MANY VULCANS ARE ON BOARD?

235
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:38,289
ASSUMING THE ENTIRE CREW
IS STILL ALIVE, 147.

236
00:16:38,289 --> 00:16:41,083
IF I'M NOT MISTAKEN,
THE LAUNCH BAY'S ON THIS LEVEL.

237
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:43,461
MAYBE WE CAN USE
ONE OF<i> THEIR</i> SHUTTLES.

238
00:16:43,461 --> 00:16:44,671
THE BAY'S DEPRESSURIZED,

239
00:16:44,671 --> 00:16:46,464
PROBABLY FROM
AN ASTEROID IMPACT.

240
00:16:46,464 --> 00:16:48,382
WE HAVE TO GET BACK TO<i> OUR</i> POD.

241
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:50,092
THAT'LL BE DIFFICULT.

242
00:16:50,092 --> 00:16:52,637
ALL FOUR BULKHEADS LEADING
TO THE AIRLOCK HAVE BEEN SEALED.

243
00:16:52,637 --> 00:16:54,388
[ BANGING ]

244
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:57,016
WE SHOULD KEEP MOVING.
HOW'S YOUR ARM?

245
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:58,392
IT'S FINE, SIR.

246
00:16:58,392 --> 00:17:00,353
HE'S LOSING A LOT OF BLOOD,
CAPTAIN.

247
00:17:00,353 --> 00:17:02,271
WE'VE GOT TO TREAT THIS WOUND.

248
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:03,314
HOW FAR TO THEIR SICKBAY?

249
00:17:03,314 --> 00:17:05,483
IT'S TWO DECKS UP.

250
00:17:05,483 --> 00:17:06,985
LET'S GO.

251
00:17:08,778 --> 00:17:10,530
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

252
00:17:10,530 --> 00:17:14,367
SINCE WE'VE COME ABOARD,
I'VE BEEN EXPERIENCING ANXIETY.

253
00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:18,204
WHATEVER'S HAPPENED TO THIS CREW
MAY BE STARTING TO AFFECT ME.

254
00:17:18,204 --> 00:17:19,789
WE'LL GET YOU OUT OF HERE
AS SOON AS WE CAN.

255
00:17:29,131 --> 00:17:31,885
THIS ONE'S MORE ISOLATED.

256
00:17:31,885 --> 00:17:35,179
AND I'M READING LARGE DEPOSITS
NEAR THE SURFACE.

257
00:17:35,179 --> 00:17:37,139
CAN YOU SET US DOWN?

258
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:40,142
THERE ISN'T A FLAT SPOT
MUCH BIGGER THAN MY QUARTERS.

259
00:17:40,142 --> 00:17:43,479
AH, YOU'RE THE PILOT.
IT'S YOUR CALL.

260
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:46,273
LET'S GO.

261
00:17:46,273 --> 00:17:49,193
I'M MATCHING
THE ROTATIONAL VELOCITY.

262
00:17:49,193 --> 00:17:50,862
LOOKING GOOD.

263
00:17:50,862 --> 00:17:53,489
200 METERS.

264
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:55,282
YOU'RE DRIFTING TO THE LEFT.

265
00:17:55,282 --> 00:17:56,450
GOT IT.

266
00:18:02,665 --> 00:18:06,419
[ BEEPING ]

267
00:18:06,419 --> 00:18:08,838
I HOPE YOU WON'T WRITE
THAT LANDING UP IN YOUR LOG.

268
00:18:08,838 --> 00:18:10,214
ARE YOU KIDDING?

269
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:12,258
I'M GONNA RECOMMEND
THEY GIVE YOU A MEDAL.

270
00:18:15,762 --> 00:18:17,764
LET'S TRY TO MAKE THIS QUICK.

271
00:18:31,736 --> 00:18:32,946
[ GRUNTS ]

272
00:18:38,117 --> 00:18:39,535
[ GROANS ]

273
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:48,502
ANY IDEA WHAT'S CAUSING THIS?

274
00:18:48,502 --> 00:18:50,212
I'M NOT A DOCTOR.

275
00:18:53,091 --> 00:18:55,301
BUT YOU ARE MY SCIENCE OFFICER.

276
00:18:55,301 --> 00:18:57,428
I NEED TO KNOW
I CAN DEPEND ON YOU.

277
00:18:58,596 --> 00:18:59,806
I'LL DO MY BEST.

278
00:19:02,266 --> 00:19:03,810
HIS NAME IS SOLIN.

279
00:19:03,810 --> 00:19:06,813
WHEN I SERVED HERE,
HE WAS THE CHIEF ENGINEER.

280
00:19:06,813 --> 00:19:08,188
I KNEW HIM.

281
00:19:08,188 --> 00:19:10,024
[ GASPS ]

282
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,111
CAN YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

283
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:18,532
SUBCOMMANDER T'POL.

284
00:19:18,532 --> 00:19:20,200
WE SERVED TOGETHER.

285
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:23,121
AAAAH!

286
00:19:23,121 --> 00:19:24,872
DON'T YOU RECOGNIZE ME?

287
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:26,457
[ GROANING ]

288
00:19:30,003 --> 00:19:31,545
WE'RE HERE TO HELP YOU,

289
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:33,756
BUT WE NEED TO KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR CREW.

290
00:19:33,756 --> 00:19:35,800
[ GRUNTING ]

291
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:38,011
SOLIN, LOOK AT ME.

292
00:19:39,053 --> 00:19:41,722
SOMETHING HAS MADE YOU VERY ILL.

293
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:45,059
YOU'VE LOST CONTROL.

294
00:19:45,059 --> 00:19:46,644
TELL ME WHAT HAPPENED.

295
00:19:48,312 --> 00:19:49,355
TELL ME!

296
00:19:49,355 --> 00:19:50,606
[ GRUNTING ]

297
00:19:53,484 --> 00:19:55,235
THIS IS GOING TO HAPPEN TO ME.

298
00:19:55,235 --> 00:19:57,196
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.

299
00:19:57,196 --> 00:19:58,489
IT'S ALREADY STARTED!

300
00:19:58,489 --> 00:20:00,449
I CAN FEEL MY CONTROL
SLIPPING AWAY.

301
00:20:00,449 --> 00:20:01,993
WE'RE GETTING YOU OFF THIS SHIP.

302
00:20:01,993 --> 00:20:03,661
IT'S TOO LATE.

303
00:20:03,661 --> 00:20:05,663
WE'RE GOING TO TAKE THE SCANS
YOU MADE BACK TO PHLOX

304
00:20:05,663 --> 00:20:07,414
AND FIGURE OUT
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE.

305
00:20:07,414 --> 00:20:11,377
BUT FIRST, WE HAVE TO
GET TO THE SHUTTLE.

306
00:20:13,171 --> 00:20:15,589
HOW DO YOU OPEN THOSE BULKHEADS?

307
00:20:19,510 --> 00:20:21,303
THE BULKHEADS.

308
00:20:25,141 --> 00:20:29,311
THERE'S AN AUXILIARY CONTROL
ROOM ON THE ENGINEERING DECK.

309
00:20:29,311 --> 00:20:30,688
OKAY.

310
00:20:34,901 --> 00:20:37,987
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

311
00:20:39,446 --> 00:20:40,907
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

312
00:20:40,907 --> 00:20:43,076
T'POL.

313
00:20:43,076 --> 00:20:44,410
WE HAVE TO KEEP MOVING.

314
00:20:46,495 --> 00:20:48,455
I DON'T NEED YOUR HELP.

315
00:20:52,418 --> 00:20:54,378
[ DOOR OPENS ]

316
00:21:01,301 --> 00:21:04,722
TWO MORE BIOSIGNS
50 METERS BEYOND THAT HATCH.

317
00:21:04,722 --> 00:21:07,058
IT'S THE ONLY WAY
TO THE ENGINEERING DECK.

318
00:21:07,058 --> 00:21:09,351
WE'LL GO DEAL WITH THEM.
STAY WITH HER, HAWKINS.

319
00:21:09,351 --> 00:21:10,477
AYE, SIR.

320
00:21:20,571 --> 00:21:23,074
WATER?

321
00:21:23,074 --> 00:21:25,159
NO OFFENSE, BUT YOU LOOK
LIKE YOU COULD USE SOME.

322
00:21:37,337 --> 00:21:38,965
THANK YOU.

323
00:21:40,716 --> 00:21:42,718
I APOLOGIZE FOR THE WAY
I REACTED BEFORE.

324
00:21:42,718 --> 00:21:45,930
YOU WERE RIGHT,
THIS IS A RESCUE MISSION.

325
00:21:47,056 --> 00:21:49,683
MAY I ASK YOU A QUESTION?

326
00:21:49,683 --> 00:21:52,061
HOW IS IT POSSIBLE THAT
THIS CREW COULD TURN SO VIOLENT

327
00:21:52,061 --> 00:21:54,521
WHEN VULCANS AREN'T
SUPPOSED TO HAVE EMOTIONS?

328
00:21:55,773 --> 00:21:57,942
A COMMON MISCONCEPTION.

329
00:21:57,942 --> 00:21:59,359
WE HAVE EMOTIONS.

330
00:21:59,359 --> 00:22:04,364
WE SIMPLY KEEP THEM SUPPRESSED,
UNDER CONTROL.

331
00:22:04,364 --> 00:22:07,910
SOMETHING HAS OBVIOUSLY CAUSED
THEM TO LOSE THAT CONTROL.

332
00:22:07,910 --> 00:22:09,912
WHY WOULD THEY WANT TO KILL US?

333
00:22:12,331 --> 00:22:14,041
THERE WAS A TIME IN THE PAST

334
00:22:14,041 --> 00:22:18,378
WHEN WE WERE
AN EXTREMELY VIOLENT RACE.

335
00:22:19,630 --> 00:22:22,049
WE NEARLY DESTROYED OURSELVES.

336
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:27,013
PARANOIA AND HOMICIDAL RAGE
WERE COMMON.

337
00:22:34,979 --> 00:22:36,730
5 METERS.

338
00:22:58,002 --> 00:22:59,879
[ GRUNTS ]

339
00:23:13,142 --> 00:23:14,768
ANY MORE WHERE THEY CAME FROM?

340
00:23:14,768 --> 00:23:15,853
[ BEEPS ]

341
00:23:15,853 --> 00:23:17,646
NOT AT THE MOMENT.

342
00:23:22,360 --> 00:23:23,694
ARCHER TO HAWKINS.

343
00:23:23,694 --> 00:23:25,238
GO AHEAD, SIR.

344
00:23:25,238 --> 00:23:26,488
WE'RE ALL CLEAR.

345
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:29,158
UNDERSTOOD.
WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

346
00:23:29,158 --> 00:23:32,745
I HEARD ABOUT THE ACCIDENT
YOU AND T'POL HAD IN THE LAB.

347
00:23:32,745 --> 00:23:34,872
AW, IT WAS MINOR.

348
00:23:34,872 --> 00:23:36,874
[ GRUNTS ]

349
00:23:36,874 --> 00:23:38,876
NOTHING TO WRITE HOME ABOUT.

350
00:23:38,876 --> 00:23:41,587
BUT YOU'RE SURE THIS STUFF
IS SAFE TO BRING ON BOARD?

351
00:23:41,587 --> 00:23:43,005
DON'T WORRY.

352
00:23:43,005 --> 00:23:45,216
IT ONLY TENDS TO BLOW UP
IN ITS LIQUID STATE.

353
00:23:45,216 --> 00:23:47,301
[ RUMBLING ]

354
00:23:51,055 --> 00:23:52,390
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

355
00:23:52,390 --> 00:23:53,724
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> TO COMMANDER TUCKER.

356
00:23:53,724 --> 00:23:55,101
GO AHEAD.

357
00:23:55,101 --> 00:23:56,643
SIR, WE'VE JUST PICKED UP
A SPATIAL ANOMALY

358
00:23:56,643 --> 00:23:57,686
AT YOUR COORDINATES.

359
00:23:57,686 --> 00:23:59,021
WE SAW IT.

360
00:23:59,021 --> 00:24:00,689
IT'S ALTERED THE COURSE
OF THE ASTEROID.

361
00:24:00,689 --> 00:24:03,276
YOU'RE HEADING INTO
A DENSER PART OF THE FIELD.

362
00:24:13,953 --> 00:24:15,537
GRAB A SEAT, COMMANDER.

363
00:24:15,537 --> 00:24:16,997
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.

364
00:24:16,997 --> 00:24:19,208
JUST GET US
THE HELL OUT OF HERE!

365
00:24:19,208 --> 00:24:20,626
[ THUDDING ]

366
00:24:28,842 --> 00:24:31,011
THE STARBOARD THRUSTER'S
FAILING!

367
00:24:31,011 --> 00:24:33,264
THERE'S DEBRIS
IN THE INTAKE MANIFOLD.

368
00:24:33,264 --> 00:24:35,266
CAN YOU PURGE IT?

369
00:24:44,858 --> 00:24:45,818
[ BEEPING ]

370
00:24:45,818 --> 00:24:47,194
WE'RE CLEAR.

371
00:24:47,194 --> 00:24:49,071
BUT WE'VE ONLY GOT
ONE THRUSTER LEFT.

372
00:24:49,071 --> 00:24:50,488
CAN YOU GET US HOME?

373
00:24:50,488 --> 00:24:51,991
I THINK SO.

374
00:24:51,991 --> 00:24:53,491
<i>SHUTTLEPOD 2</i> TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

375
00:24:53,491 --> 00:24:55,077
GO AHEAD, COMMANDER.

376
00:24:55,077 --> 00:24:56,954
WE'RE ON OUR WAY BACK,
BUT WE'VE TAKEN DAMAGE.

377
00:24:56,954 --> 00:24:59,290
ALERT THE LAUNCH BAY CREW TO
GET READY FOR A ROUGH DOCKING.

378
00:24:59,290 --> 00:25:00,540
UNDERSTOOD.

379
00:25:17,599 --> 00:25:19,226
SECURE THE DOOR.

380
00:25:27,485 --> 00:25:30,070
THE TRANSCEIVER'S BEEN DAMAGED.

381
00:25:30,070 --> 00:25:32,198
ANY CHANCE OF REPAIRING IT?

382
00:25:32,198 --> 00:25:34,658
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

383
00:25:34,658 --> 00:25:36,369
-T'POL?
-WHAT?

384
00:25:38,162 --> 00:25:40,206
ANY CHANCE OF REPAIRING IT?

385
00:25:42,333 --> 00:25:45,378
THERE'S AN AUXILIARY
TRANSMITTER.

386
00:25:45,378 --> 00:25:46,712
IF I CAN GET ACCESS TO IT,

387
00:25:46,712 --> 00:25:49,048
WE MAY BE ABLE
TO CONTACT<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

388
00:25:49,048 --> 00:25:52,259
SIR, I'VE ENCRYPTED
THE LOCKING CODES.

389
00:25:52,259 --> 00:25:55,346
BUT IF THEY'RE DETERMINED
TO GET IN...

390
00:26:00,100 --> 00:26:02,769
LOOKS LIKE THE IMPULSE ASSEMBLY
TOOK A BEATING.

391
00:26:02,769 --> 00:26:04,730
OPEN UP THE ENGINE HOUSINGS
AND RUN A DIAGNOSTIC.

392
00:26:04,730 --> 00:26:07,107
-[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
-BRIDGE TO COMMANDER TUCKER.

393
00:26:10,903 --> 00:26:12,446
TUCKER HERE.

394
00:26:12,446 --> 00:26:14,490
WE'RE RECEIVING A TRANSMISSION
FROM THE CAPTAIN.

395
00:26:14,490 --> 00:26:15,573
IT SOUNDS URGENT.

396
00:26:15,573 --> 00:26:16,574
ROUTE IT DOWN HERE.

397
00:26:16,574 --> 00:26:18,369
GO AHEAD, CAPTAIN.

398
00:26:18,369 --> 00:26:21,163
TRIP, WE'RE GOING TO NEED SOME
HELP GETTING OFF THIS SHIP.

399
00:26:21,163 --> 00:26:22,789
HOW FAST CAN YOU BE HERE?

400
00:26:22,789 --> 00:26:25,459
POD 2 TOOK SOME DAMAGE
IN THE ASTEROID FIELD, SIR.

401
00:26:25,459 --> 00:26:27,086
WE'RE LOOKING AT...

402
00:26:27,086 --> 00:26:29,296
A COUPLE HOURS BEFORE
WE CAN LAUNCH AGAIN.

403
00:26:29,296 --> 00:26:30,381
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

404
00:26:30,381 --> 00:26:33,008
IT'S THE VULCAN CREW.

405
00:26:33,008 --> 00:26:34,510
SOMETHING'S WRONG WITH THEM.

406
00:26:34,510 --> 00:26:36,970
WE'RE GOING TO TRANSMIT
SOME BIODATA.

407
00:26:36,970 --> 00:26:39,432
TELL PHLOX
TO START ANALYZING IT.

408
00:26:39,432 --> 00:26:42,309
SEE IF THERE'S ANYTHING
WE CAN DO TO HELP THESE PEOPLE.

409
00:26:42,309 --> 00:26:44,395
ACKNOWLEDGED.
ANYTHING ELSE?

410
00:26:44,395 --> 00:26:46,272
JUST GET THAT SHUTTLE FLYING.

411
00:26:46,272 --> 00:26:47,314
AYE, SIR.

412
00:26:47,314 --> 00:26:48,899
ARCHER OUT.

413
00:26:48,899 --> 00:26:51,609
YOU HEARD THE CAPTAIN.
GET A REPAIR TEAM DOWN HERE.

414
00:26:57,575 --> 00:27:00,119
THE BULKHEAD CONTROLS
WERE SEVERED ON DECK 9.

415
00:27:00,119 --> 00:27:02,996
I'VE REROUTED THEM
THROUGH THE AUXILIARY GRID.

416
00:27:02,996 --> 00:27:06,708
MR. REED, ARE YOU FINISHED
WITH THOSE ACTUATOR CIRCUITS?

417
00:27:06,708 --> 00:27:08,919
THEY'VE ALL BEEN REALIGNED.

418
00:27:10,212 --> 00:27:11,964
-[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]
-[ GRUNTS ]

419
00:27:11,964 --> 00:27:13,299
YOU OKAY?

420
00:27:13,299 --> 00:27:15,175
WHAT DID YOU DO?

421
00:27:15,175 --> 00:27:17,553
I-I REALIGNED THE CIRCUITS,
JUST LIKE YOU ASKED ME.

422
00:27:17,553 --> 00:27:18,678
[ GRUNTS ]

423
00:27:18,678 --> 00:27:21,348
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

424
00:27:21,348 --> 00:27:24,726
THESE AREN'T
SEQUENCED CORRECTLY!

425
00:27:24,726 --> 00:27:27,020
YOU OVERLOADED
THE LOCKING MECHANISM!

426
00:27:27,020 --> 00:27:30,774
THEN WE'LL HAVE TO
TRY SOMETHING ELSE.

427
00:27:30,774 --> 00:27:35,028
IT'S POINTLESS.
THE CIRCUITS ARE DAMAGED!

428
00:27:35,028 --> 00:27:36,155
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

429
00:27:36,155 --> 00:27:38,115
I SHOULD HAVE BEEN WATCHING HIM!

430
00:27:42,578 --> 00:27:44,955
YOU DIDN'T WANT ME TO SEE.

431
00:27:49,543 --> 00:27:52,921
NOW I KNOW WHAT YOU WERE DOING
IN THE COMMAND CENTER.

432
00:27:52,921 --> 00:27:54,089
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

433
00:27:54,089 --> 00:27:56,383
THE XINDI STAR CHARTS.

434
00:27:56,383 --> 00:27:59,303
YOU WERE ANALYZING THEM
BEHIND MY BACK,

435
00:27:59,303 --> 00:28:01,096
UNDERMINING MY WORK.

436
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:04,724
NO ONE'S TRYING
TO SABOTAGE YOUR WORK.

437
00:28:04,724 --> 00:28:09,146
WE SHOULD ALL JUST FOCUS ON
GETTING OFF THIS SHIP SAFELY.

438
00:28:09,146 --> 00:28:12,358
THERE MIGHT BE ANOTHER WAY, SIR.

439
00:28:12,358 --> 00:28:14,151
IF WE OVERLOAD THE POWER GRID,

440
00:28:14,151 --> 00:28:16,612
IT WOULD DISRUPT THE SYSTEMS
ALL OVER THE SHIP,

441
00:28:16,612 --> 00:28:18,405
INCLUDING
THE BULKHEAD MECHANISMS.

442
00:28:18,405 --> 00:28:20,782
THE WARP REACTOR
IS UNSTABLE AS IT IS.

443
00:28:20,782 --> 00:28:24,203
DISRUPTING MAIN POWER COULD SHUT
DOWN THE ANTIMATTER CONTAINMENT.

444
00:28:24,203 --> 00:28:26,079
YOU'D CAUSE A REACTOR BREACH.

445
00:28:26,079 --> 00:28:28,457
I DON'T THINK
WE HAVE MUCH OF A CHOICE.

446
00:28:34,838 --> 00:28:36,465
YOU WANT TO KILL ALL OF US.

447
00:28:38,509 --> 00:28:41,303
YOU DON'T TRUST VULCANS.

448
00:28:41,303 --> 00:28:42,929
YOU NEVER HAVE.

449
00:28:42,929 --> 00:28:46,016
SIR, THAT PISTOL'S SET TO KILL.

450
00:28:47,226 --> 00:28:48,602
GIVE ME THE WEAPON.

451
00:28:48,602 --> 00:28:51,271
DON'T THINK I'VE FORGOTTEN.

452
00:28:51,271 --> 00:28:53,524
YOU BLAMED US
FOR HOLDING YOU BACK,

453
00:28:53,524 --> 00:28:57,110
FOR UNDERMINING
YOUR FATHER'S WORK.

454
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:59,613
NOW YOU DECIDED TO TAKE REVENGE.

455
00:29:01,615 --> 00:29:02,949
I'LL FIRE!

456
00:29:02,949 --> 00:29:06,537
LISTEN TO ME.
THIS IS A RESCUE MISSION.

457
00:29:06,537 --> 00:29:08,830
WE'RE HERE TO SAVE THESE PEOPLE.

458
00:29:08,830 --> 00:29:11,041
YOU'RE LYING.

459
00:29:11,041 --> 00:29:12,501
YOU WANT TO KILL THEM.

460
00:29:12,501 --> 00:29:15,795
IF THAT'S TRUE...

461
00:29:15,795 --> 00:29:19,508
THEN WHY WOULD I KEEP
OUR WEAPONS ON STUN?

462
00:29:19,508 --> 00:29:21,468
IT'S NOT LOGICAL.

463
00:29:21,468 --> 00:29:22,553
[ BANGING ON DOOR ]

464
00:29:22,553 --> 00:29:24,096
[ GRUNTS ]

465
00:29:26,515 --> 00:29:28,058
[ BANGING CONTINUES ]

466
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:32,438
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

467
00:29:32,438 --> 00:29:35,190
T'POL AND I HAVE BEEN WORKING
WITH TRELLIUM FOR WEEKS.

468
00:29:35,190 --> 00:29:36,650
SHE HASN'T SHOWN ANY SYMPTOMS.

469
00:29:36,650 --> 00:29:38,485
I DON'T IMAGINE SHE WOULD HAVE.

470
00:29:38,485 --> 00:29:40,820
DESPITE YOUR BEST EFFORTS, YOU
WEREN'T ABLE TO SYNTHESIZE IT

471
00:29:40,820 --> 00:29:42,698
IN ANY SIGNIFICANT QUANTITIES.

472
00:29:42,698 --> 00:29:44,824
THE CREW OF THE<i> SELEYA,</i> HOWEVER,
HAD THE MISFORTUNE

473
00:29:44,824 --> 00:29:48,704
OF WANDERING INTO AN ASTEROID
FIELD FILLED WITH THE COMPOUND.

474
00:29:48,704 --> 00:29:50,748
TRELLIUM-D
IS A POTENT NEUROTOXIN

475
00:29:50,748 --> 00:29:52,124
TO THE VULCAN NERVOUS SYSTEM.

476
00:29:52,124 --> 00:29:53,959
IT DISRUPTS
THE SYNAPTIC PATHWAYS

477
00:29:53,959 --> 00:29:56,211
THAT ALLOW THEM
TO CONTROL EMOTIONS.

478
00:29:56,211 --> 00:29:59,423
UNFORTUNATELY, THE RATE OF DECAY
IS ACCELERATING.

479
00:30:09,057 --> 00:30:10,768
IS IT TOO LATE?

480
00:30:10,768 --> 00:30:13,019
I CAN TREAT HER, BUT I NEED TO
BEGIN SYNAPTIC REGENERATION

481
00:30:13,019 --> 00:30:15,314
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

482
00:30:15,314 --> 00:30:16,982
WHAT ABOUT THE VULCAN CREW?

483
00:30:16,982 --> 00:30:18,317
[ STATIC BUZZING ]

484
00:30:18,317 --> 00:30:19,985
PHLOX, DO YOU READ ME?

485
00:30:19,985 --> 00:30:21,861
I'M AFRAID THERE'S NOTHING
WE CAN DO FOR THE OTHERS.

486
00:30:21,861 --> 00:30:23,905
THEY'VE BEEN EXPOSED
FOR TOO LONG.

487
00:30:23,905 --> 00:30:25,532
THE NEUROLOGICAL DAMAGE
IS IRREVERSIBLE.

488
00:30:25,532 --> 00:30:26,866
THEY'RE DYING, CAPTAIN.

489
00:30:26,866 --> 00:30:29,703
HE'S LYING!
HE WANTS THEM ALL TO DIE.

490
00:30:29,703 --> 00:30:32,372
DOCTOR, THERE ARE
OVER 140 PEOPLE ON THIS SHIP.

491
00:30:32,372 --> 00:30:34,166
I'M SORRY, BUT THEY'VE BEEN...

492
00:30:34,166 --> 00:30:35,501
[ STATIC BUZZING ]

493
00:30:35,501 --> 00:30:37,586
<i>ENTERPRISE.</i>

494
00:30:37,586 --> 00:30:39,254
PHLOX, DO YOU HEAR ME?
RESPOND.

495
00:30:39,254 --> 00:30:41,173
THEY'VE SHUT
THE COM SYSTEM DOWN.

496
00:30:41,173 --> 00:30:45,427
CAPTAIN, THEY'RE FLOODING THE
COMPARTMENT WITH HEXAFLUORINE.

497
00:30:45,427 --> 00:30:47,763
[ GASPS ]

498
00:30:56,355 --> 00:30:57,606
[ ALL COUGHING ]

499
00:30:57,606 --> 00:30:59,316
SHUT IT OFF.

500
00:30:59,316 --> 00:31:01,234
I CAN'T. THEY'VE BYPASSED
THE ENVIRONMENTAL CONTROLS.

501
00:31:01,234 --> 00:31:04,697
THEY WON'T LET YOU
DESTROY THIS SHIP.

502
00:31:04,697 --> 00:31:08,450
AFTER YOU INITIATE THE OVERLOAD,
HOW LONG DO WE HAVE?

503
00:31:08,450 --> 00:31:12,078
[ COUGHING ]
15 MINUTES, MAYBE LESS.

504
00:31:12,078 --> 00:31:13,622
NO!

505
00:31:13,622 --> 00:31:15,040
YOU HEARD WHAT THE DOCTOR SAID.

506
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:17,000
THEY CAN'T BE SAVED,
BUT YOU CAN.

507
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,126
MURDERER!

508
00:31:18,126 --> 00:31:20,170
HELP ME GET HER OUT OF HERE.

509
00:31:23,298 --> 00:31:24,424
[ GRUNTS ]

510
00:31:24,424 --> 00:31:26,301
[ COUGHING ]

511
00:31:26,301 --> 00:31:27,386
MALCOLM?

512
00:31:27,386 --> 00:31:28,721
JUST ABOUT THERE.

513
00:31:28,721 --> 00:31:29,763
COME ON.

514
00:31:29,763 --> 00:31:31,431
[ COUGHING ]

515
00:31:31,431 --> 00:31:32,641
CLIMB!

516
00:31:38,564 --> 00:31:40,607
MALCOLM!

517
00:31:40,607 --> 00:31:42,025
[ BEEPING ]

518
00:31:42,025 --> 00:31:45,070
[ ALARM BLARING ]

519
00:32:39,249 --> 00:32:41,418
WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME!

520
00:32:41,418 --> 00:32:44,463
NO! NO!

521
00:32:44,463 --> 00:32:45,923
NO!

522
00:32:45,923 --> 00:32:49,175
YOU CAN'T STAY HERE!

523
00:33:01,688 --> 00:33:03,482
ANOTHER 20 METERS.

524
00:33:08,779 --> 00:33:09,988
CAPTAIN!

525
00:33:20,791 --> 00:33:22,626
HOW WERE YOU AT THE LONG JUMP?

526
00:33:28,924 --> 00:33:30,008
WATCH HER.

527
00:33:30,008 --> 00:33:31,677
REED.

528
00:33:41,102 --> 00:33:44,314
[ GRUNTS ]

529
00:33:44,314 --> 00:33:45,482
AAH!

530
00:33:58,161 --> 00:34:00,789
COME ON.

531
00:34:00,789 --> 00:34:01,874
YOU CAN MAKE IT.

532
00:34:01,874 --> 00:34:03,625
GET AWAY FROM ME.

533
00:34:03,625 --> 00:34:05,126
IT'S OKAY.
I'LL HELP YOU.

534
00:34:05,126 --> 00:34:06,962
YOU TOUCH ME, AND I'LL KILL YOU!

535
00:34:07,963 --> 00:34:09,255
AAH!

536
00:34:39,745 --> 00:34:42,039
[ LASER FIRE ]

537
00:34:43,665 --> 00:34:45,375
[ GRUNTING ]

538
00:34:45,375 --> 00:34:47,126
GO!

539
00:34:55,468 --> 00:34:57,095
I SAID GO!

540
00:35:10,984 --> 00:35:12,903
GIVE ME A HAND!

541
00:35:12,903 --> 00:35:14,362
[ GRUNTING ]

542
00:35:55,028 --> 00:35:57,280
[ BEEPING ]

543
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:58,615
WHAT'S WRONG?

544
00:35:58,615 --> 00:36:01,451
I CAN'T RELEASE
THE DOCKING CLAMPS.

545
00:36:01,451 --> 00:36:03,411
FULL POWER TO THRUSTERS.

546
00:36:04,788 --> 00:36:06,873
-[ BEEPING ]
-WE'RE BEING HAILED.

547
00:36:10,919 --> 00:36:12,295
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT, CAPTAIN?

548
00:36:12,295 --> 00:36:13,755
THE DOCKING CLAMPS ARE JAMMED.

549
00:36:13,755 --> 00:36:15,007
WE COULD USE A HAND.

550
00:36:15,007 --> 00:36:16,133
STAND BY.

551
00:36:24,016 --> 00:36:25,600
YOU'RE CLEAR, SIR.

552
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:27,894
THE SHIP'S ABOUT TO BLOW.
GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE!

553
00:36:37,904 --> 00:36:39,948
[ RUMBLING ]

554
00:36:42,784 --> 00:36:44,786
ARCHER TO<i> SHUTTLEPOD 2.</i>

555
00:36:44,786 --> 00:36:46,371
ARE YOU STILL IN ONE PIECE?

556
00:36:46,371 --> 00:36:47,789
WE'RE FINE, SIR.

557
00:36:47,789 --> 00:36:49,415
SEE YOU BACK ON<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

558
00:36:49,415 --> 00:36:50,792
[ SIGHS ]

559
00:37:00,677 --> 00:37:03,013
WE'VE GOT OVER 60 KILOS.

560
00:37:03,013 --> 00:37:05,932
IT SHOULD BE ENOUGH
TO LINE THE FORWARD HULL.

561
00:37:11,938 --> 00:37:15,942
MAY BE A WHILE BEFORE PHLOX
FINDS A WAY TO INOCULATE T'POL.

562
00:37:17,986 --> 00:37:22,032
TAKE THIS TO CARGO BAY ONE,
STORE IT IN A BIOHAZARD LOCKER.

563
00:37:22,032 --> 00:37:23,950
AYE, SIR.

564
00:37:26,953 --> 00:37:28,830
HOW'D IT GO?

565
00:37:28,830 --> 00:37:30,790
YOU GOT HER OUT IN TIME,
CAPTAIN.

566
00:37:30,790 --> 00:37:33,334
HER SYNAPTIC PATHWAYS
ARE MENDING NICELY.

567
00:37:33,334 --> 00:37:35,003
BUT IT WILL BE A FEW DAYS

568
00:37:35,003 --> 00:37:38,673
BEFORE SHE FULLY REGAINS
CONTROL OF HER EMOTIONS.

569
00:37:38,673 --> 00:37:40,592
I'D LIKE TO TALK WITH HER.

570
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:51,436
[ HISSES ]

571
00:37:54,355 --> 00:37:56,691
[ EXHALES ]

572
00:37:59,945 --> 00:38:01,947
PHLOX WAS ABLE TO HELP YOU.

573
00:38:01,947 --> 00:38:03,531
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

574
00:38:04,699 --> 00:38:06,367
THE<i> SELEYA?</i>

575
00:38:08,828 --> 00:38:10,329
IT WAS DESTROYED.

576
00:38:10,329 --> 00:38:13,291
I'M SORRY,
BUT I DIDN'T HAVE A CHOICE.

577
00:38:13,291 --> 00:38:14,751
THEY WERE BEYOND HELP.

578
00:38:14,751 --> 00:38:17,545
THEIR FATE WAS SEALED
LONG BEFORE WE ARRIVED.

579
00:38:19,256 --> 00:38:21,049
PLEASE DON'T BE LONG.

580
00:38:28,765 --> 00:38:31,893
WAS COMMANDER TUCKER SUCCESSFUL?

581
00:38:31,893 --> 00:38:34,980
YES AND NO.

582
00:38:34,980 --> 00:38:39,109
HE COLLECTED
A GOOD SUPPLY OF TRELLIUM.

583
00:38:39,109 --> 00:38:43,238
BUT IT TURNS OUT IT WAS TRELLIUM
THAT POISONED THE VULCAN CREW.

584
00:38:44,781 --> 00:38:46,283
AND YOU.

585
00:38:52,538 --> 00:38:55,458
IT'S ESSENTIAL
YOU PROTECT THIS SHIP.

586
00:38:57,669 --> 00:39:00,588
LEAVE ME ON THE NEXT
HABITABLE PLANET.

587
00:39:00,588 --> 00:39:02,090
I'M NOT GOING TO DO THAT.

588
00:39:04,968 --> 00:39:08,346
YOU CAN'T ALLOW YOUR CONCERN
FOR A SINGLE CREWMAN

589
00:39:08,346 --> 00:39:10,849
TO AFFECT YOUR MISSION.

590
00:39:10,849 --> 00:39:14,019
THIS EXPANSE DESTROYED
EVERYONE ABOARD THE<i> SELEYA.</i>

591
00:39:15,603 --> 00:39:18,397
DON'T LET IT HAPPEN
TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

592
00:39:19,732 --> 00:39:21,776
WE'LL FIND A WAY THROUGH THIS.

593
00:39:24,029 --> 00:39:28,491
BUT I WON'T LEAVE ANYONE BEHIND,
NOT IF I CAN HELP IT.

594
00:39:29,951 --> 00:39:31,536
I CAN'T TRY TO SAVE HUMANITY

595
00:39:31,536 --> 00:39:34,331
WITHOUT HOLDING ON
TO WHAT MAKES ME HUMAN.

596
00:39:44,423 --> 00:39:45,925
<i>DEAD END --</i>
<i>AS FAR WEST AS SHE GOES.</i>

597
00:39:45,925 --> 00:39:47,635
SOMETHING TELLS ME
WE HAVEN'T SEEN THE LAST

598
00:39:47,635 --> 00:39:50,347
OF THE DETECTIVE IN THE BOW TIE.

599
00:39:50,347 --> 00:39:52,557
NO, HE DIED IN A HOUSE FIRE.

600
00:39:52,557 --> 00:39:54,351
AH, DID HE? HMM?

601
00:39:54,351 --> 00:39:55,894
THE AUTOPSY WAS INCONCLUSIVE.

602
00:39:55,894 --> 00:39:57,270
I WOULDN'T BE SURPRISED

603
00:39:57,270 --> 00:39:59,272
IF THE BODY BELONGED
TO THE DELIVERY MAN.

604
00:39:59,272 --> 00:40:01,149
HMM?
WITH THE STRANGE LIMP.

605
00:40:01,149 --> 00:40:03,276
YOU NEVER DID SEE HIM
LEAVE THE HOUSE.

606
00:40:03,276 --> 00:40:06,029
WHAT ABOUT THE GARDENER?
HE WAS THERE, TOO.

607
00:40:06,029 --> 00:40:07,572
TOO TALL.

608
00:40:07,572 --> 00:40:09,782
EVEN THE PRIMITIVE FORENSICS
OF THE MID-20TH CENTURY

609
00:40:09,782 --> 00:40:10,909
WOULD HAVE DETERMINED THAT.

610
00:40:10,909 --> 00:40:12,202
[ CHUCKLES ]

611
00:40:12,202 --> 00:40:15,538
PERHAPS WE SHOULD WATCH
AND FIND OUT.

612
00:40:17,374 --> 00:40:18,917
PART OF THE FUN OF A MYSTERY

613
00:40:18,917 --> 00:40:23,213
IS TRYING TO SOLVE IT
BEFORE IT ENDS, USING LOGIC.

614
00:40:23,213 --> 00:40:26,007
YOU OF ALL PEOPLE
SHOULD APPRECIATE THAT.

615
00:40:26,007 --> 00:40:29,468
THEN USE LOGIC MORE QUIETLY.

616
00:40:32,513 --> 00:40:34,099
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

617
00:40:34,099 --> 00:40:37,810
ALL HANDS REPORT TO STATIONS.
TACTICAL ALERT.

618
00:40:37,810 --> 00:40:39,145
[ CHATTERING ]

619
00:41:03,420 --> 00:41:05,213
[ GRUNTING ]

620
00:41:20,519 --> 00:41:23,564
T'POL! T'POL! T'POL!

621
00:41:23,564 --> 00:41:24,816
T'POL!

622
00:41:24,816 --> 00:41:26,484
-T'POL!
-[ GASPS ]

623
00:41:27,402 --> 00:41:29,821
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

624
00:41:29,821 --> 00:41:32,157
YOU'RE ON<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

625
00:41:33,616 --> 00:41:36,035
YOU'RE SAFE.
